      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GO FORWARD BERNY (1) turned in a better effort at Maitland last start, finishing second behind Zipping Desire (23.08) in a Maiden. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Likely to feature again. BARRY BULLPIT (5) made an eye-catching debut when showed blistering pace early and gave a sight when in the minors, beaten 5 lengths over 401m this track in 23.44. Can only be improved and looks a key chance if runs up to debut effort. KIWI FUSION (8) is a handily bred pup making his debut without a trial. Can kick off with a good run. ARCHIE'S CHOICE (2) makes debut for the Jane Mortimer kennel. Gets every chance from the inside draw. Can feature with the right run.",
